Quantum Machine Learning Project

This project represents a groundbreaking exploration into the intersection of machine learning and quantum computing. It began with the development of a classical Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) that achieved a remarkable 90% accuracy in classifying images into ten distinct categories.

The journey continues with the transformation of this classical model into a hybrid Quantum Machine Learning model. By integrating Quantum Neural Networks and quantum optimizer functions, we're investigating the effects on model accuracy, training duration, and feature selection.

This project is not just about improving accuracy, but about reshaping the landscape of machine learning. With the advancement of quantum computnpm install --legacy-peer-deps react-revealers, we're looking to harness quantum mechanics to build models that were previously unattainable.
